One challenge we faced this sprint was navigating Figma designs during development. There are many screens and flows, which made it time-consuming to identify what is actually final and required for implementation.

It would help if we could have clearer separation or labeling of dev-ready designs (for example, marking final flows or grouping relevant screens). This could reduce confusion and speed up development.


It would be helpful if stories for refinement could be shared at least one day in advance. This would give the team enough time to review the requirements beforehand and come prepared with questions or concerns.

As a result, we can have more focused and productive discussions during the refinement call, leading to better clarity and fewer follow-ups later.



